---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL, AUTHOR, FOUNDING_DATE, KNOWS_ABOUT, PUBLISHING_PRINCIPLES } from '../../lib/site';

const abs = (p: string) => new URL(p, Astro.site).href;
const aboutLd = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'AboutPage',
    name: `About ${SITE_NAME}`,
    url: abs('/sg/about/'),
    mainEntity: {
      '@type': 'Organization',
      name: SITE_NAME,
      url: SITE_URL,
      description: 'Evidence-led skincare guidance for skin in Singapore.',
      foundingDate: FOUNDING_DATE,
      knowsAbout: KNOWS_ABOUT,
      publishingPrinciples: PUBLISHING_PRINCIPLES,
    },
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="TheBeautyGPT gives evidence-led skincare answers for skin in Singapore: clear comparisons, real mechanisms, and guidance relevant to local products, prices, and climate."
  jsonLd={aboutLd}
  lang="en"
  market="sg"
  path="/about/"
>
  <article class="article">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">About</p>
      <h1>Skincare, decoded for Singapore.</h1>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>TheBeautyGPT answers one question well: <em>what actually works for my skin?</em> Most of what you find online is either vague or hard to act on. We give clear, evidence-led answers, built for skin in Singapore, the weather here, and what you can actually buy locally.</p>

        <h2>How we work</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Mechanism first.</strong> We explain <em>why</em> something works (or doesn't) before we get to products: hydrocolloid vs microneedle, actives, formulation.</li>
          <li><strong>Real comparisons.</strong> We weigh the actual options you can buy in Singapore, side by side.</li>
          <li><strong>Local reality.</strong> Prices in Singapore dollars, where to buy (Shopee, Watsons, Guardian), and what suits a hot, humid climate.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who writes and reviews this</h2>
        <p>Our articles are researched and written by the <strong>{AUTHOR.name}</strong>, a research-led team that reads dermatology sources (clinical guidance from bodies like the American Academy of Dermatology, DermNet, and the NHS) and translates it into plain English. We grade how strong the evidence actually is (strong, mixed, or preliminary) rather than presenting everything as settled.</p>
        <p>Every article is checked against our <a href="/sg/editorial-standards/">editorial standards</a>: mechanism explained, evidence graded honestly, ingredients described accurately, and no claim stretched beyond what the research supports. When the honest answer is "the evidence is weak" or "you don't need this," we say so. We do not publish under fabricated bylines.</p>
        <p>For exactly how we research, grade evidence, and review each article, plus an honest note on medical review, see <a href="/sg/how-we-review/">how we review</a>.</p>

        <h2>Not medical advice</h2>
        <p>Our content is educational. For persistent, painful, or severe skin concerns, see a doctor or a certified dermatologist.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
